{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-page-js","path":"/posts/cards/ambi-translate/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Speak clearly like never before: this is <em>Ambi Translate.</em></p>\n<!-- end excerpt -->\n<p>This project is a fictional landing page made to experiment with <a href=\"https://gohugo.io/\">Hugo</a>, which came as a result of lacking support in my usual stack for i18n. Hugo even lists their i18n support as one of the <em>Reasons They're Pretty Great, Guys:</em></p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 35.416666666666664%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/e248b8f9c0bff2ec7b87ec0c75797b2b/d99d0/hugo-polyglot.webp 240w,\n/static/e248b8f9c0bff2ec7b87ec0c75797b2b/978de/hugo-polyglot.webp 480w,\n/static/e248b8f9c0bff2ec7b87ec0c75797b2b/78b62/hugo-polyglot.webp 768w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/e248b8f9c0bff2ec7b87ec0c75797b2b/07e12/hugo-polyglot.png 240w,\n/static/e248b8f9c0bff2ec7b87ec0c75797b2b/5ca43/hugo-polyglot.png 480w,\n/static/e248b8f9c0bff2ec7b87ec0c75797b2b/31dcc/hugo-polyglot.png 768w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/e248b8f9c0bff2ec7b87ec0c75797b2b/31dcc/hugo-polyglot.png\"\n          alt=\"Hugo wants you to know that your react-i18n woes are over (Source: gohugo.io)\"\n          title=\"Hugo wants you to know that your react-i18n woes are over (Source: gohugo.io)\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Hugo wants you to know that your react-i18n woes are over (Source: gohugo.io)</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>This lacking support was mostly a result for poor documentation - while Hugo's docs are no piece of cake to digest, it was easy enough to leverage my already existing <a href=\"https://jekyllrb.com/\">Jekyll</a> experience and hack something together. It's a shame I had to, though - big players on the internet like Google and Facebook love to talk about how they're all for a richer, more inclusive web... so why isn't it easy/ier to implement?</p>\n<p>But enough about that.</p>\n<h2>About Ambi Translate</h2>\n<p><em>Ambi Translate</em> is a fictional translation service offered by fictional Google-like demigod-corporation <em>Ambi.</em> The service entered widespread use <del>because Ambi practically owns its users</del> because of the unusual habit Ambi have of assigning mascots to its services. These mascots appear in most (if not all) of Ambi's products, assuming different names and titles as they see fit.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/d17a9ef75cf95641ac00277773e33295/d99d0/harbringers.webp 240w,\n/static/d17a9ef75cf95641ac00277773e33295/978de/harbringers.webp 480w,\n/static/d17a9ef75cf95641ac00277773e33295/3ebc2/harbringers.webp 960w,\n/static/d17a9ef75cf95641ac00277773e33295/12062/harbringers.webp 1440w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/d17a9ef75cf95641ac00277773e33295/07e12/harbringers.png 240w,\n/static/d17a9ef75cf95641ac00277773e33295/5ca43/harbringers.png 480w,\n/static/d17a9ef75cf95641ac00277773e33295/4d297/harbringers.png 960w,\n/static/d17a9ef75cf95641ac00277773e33295/09904/harbringers.png 1440w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/d17a9ef75cf95641ac00277773e33295/4d297/harbringers.png\"\n          alt=\"Two of Ambi&#39;s mascots. Left: Daydream, right: Just Cause\"\n          title=\"Two of Ambi&#39;s mascots. Left: Daydream, right: Just Cause\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Two of Ambi&#39;s mascots. Left: Daydream, right: Just Cause</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Ambi styles their translation service as something groundbreaking - a literal revolution in the way the world communicates - and so they posit that these two are the <em>Harbringers of the Revolution,</em> paving the way for a new world.</p>\n<p>This overdramtic, slightly hammy rhetoric soon earned Ambi new fans, and so Ambi Translate remains well-liked and depended upon to this day.</p>\n<h2>What I Used</h2>\n<p>Translations from English to 'Nimish' were generated with my <code class=\"language-text\">nimify</code> package (<a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/nimify\">available on npm</a>) and manually copied into a Hugo <code class=\"language-text\">config.toml</code> file.</p>\n<p>The single-page layout makes heavy use of <a href=\"https://bulma.io\">Bulma</a>, and the playing of the sample voice clips is handled with <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/howler\">Howler.js</a>. The sample voice clips were generated with the use of <a href=\"http://mary.dfki.de/\">MaryTTS</a> and <a href=\"https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/typetalk/\">typetalk</a>.</p>\n<p>All in all, I learned a lot!</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Ambi Translate","date":"3-11-19"},"timeToRead":2,"wordCount":{"words":330},"parent":{"prettySize":"2.55 kB","name":"ambi-translate"},"excerpt":"Speak clearly like never before: this is Ambi Translate."}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/posts/cards/ambi-translate/"}}}